title: Twitter couldn't believe how perfect Georgia and Alex were for each other on First Dates
text:
Twitter couldn't believe how perfect Georgia and Alex were for each other on First Dates Twitter couldn't believe how perfect Georgia and Alex were for each other on First Dates 
It’s that time of week again, guys! #firstdates …..lets see if I can pick up any tips 😁😂😂 
— Lisa (@X_Lisa1972_X) October 22, 2015 
Hugo reappeared on tonight’s show after failing to “fancy” his previous date. Awk. Well we’re glad Hugo’s got to the bottom of what he’s looking for in a date… 😂 #FirstDates pic.twitter.com/wBsFDreTti 
— First Dates (@C4FirstDates) October 22, 2015 
He was paired up with Opera singing beauty Olympia, and the two seemed made for each other. "Olympia" is a posh enough name for him. #FirstDates 
Hugo again was his eccentric self. Is Hugo being played by Jim Carey, doing an English-accented version of Ace Ventura? #FirstDates 
— Inspector Morose (@InspectorMorose) October 22, 2015 Hugo is the real life every-character-that-Hugh-Grant-has-ever-played x 100 #firstdates 
— Emily Blunden (@atticusandfinch) October 22, 2015 
But unfortunately, the date ended on a bad note, as Hugo didn’t feel a “spark”. 
Next up was Jacqui & Ricky. Maybe save that until after dinner eh Jacqui? 😅 #FirstDates pic.twitter.com/rh1JVreBfp 
— First Dates (@C4FirstDates) October 22, 2015 
Who you may recognise from the episode previews from previous weeks. 
— Auntie Pegg (@AuntiePegg) October 22, 2015 
But again, sparks didn’t fly here either. Ah no #FirstDates noooo! The post meal friend zone burn. 
— Kachela (@KachelaMurray) October 22, 2015 
And things didn’t look any better for Newcastle beaut Georgia who was stood-up on her date. The guy who stood up the girl from Newcastle on #firstdates must be kicking himself right now, she is stunning, I would def take her out 
— Ashley Picton (@ashpicton) October 22, 2015 
https://twitter.com/Carterface_/status/657310279462711296 
Just when you thought romance had died, in walked the handsome, and very sweet Alex who took Georgia’s fancy. Unfortunately, he was there to date someone else but they didn’t seem to be hitting it off. Does Alex's date ever stop talking? No wonder she says she feels like she's talking to a brick wall #cantgetawordinedgeways #firstdates 
— Tracey Moore (@KissAnotherFrog) October 22, 2015 
But fear not! The show revealed that next week Alex and Georgia will be paired up on a date together instead! How cute! Yes! Can't wait to see Georgia & Alex go on a date! 😊👏 Woop! #FirstDates 
— Maya Simone (@mayasphere) October 22, 2015 you have no idea how happy I am that they've hooked that girl and guy up for next week! love it! #feelingsoppy #firstdates 
And in other lovey-dovey news, Steven went on a date with a woman who didn’t mind how in love with his Nan he is. Guy from Wrexham who loves his nan is so sweet I can't bare it! #FirstDates 
— Kay Dekker (@kay_way) October 22, 2015 #FirstDates You know exactly who I'm talking about pic.twitter.com/OweWOX7lna 
— mof gimmers (@mofgimmers) October 22, 2015 
Apparently Anna and Steven’s Nan are now knitting buddies. 
— First Dates (@C4FirstDates) October 22, 2015 Share article
